WEBVTT

1
00:00:11.636 --> 00:00:15.724
<i>It's been two days</i>
<i>since Min Ho and I crashed and burned.</i>

2
00:00:15.807 --> 00:00:20.353
<i>At least. I think it's been two days.</i>
<i>I've lost all track of time.</i>

3
00:00:20.437 --> 00:00:22.480
<i>I now measure the day</i>
<i>in the number of times</i>

4
00:00:22.564 --> 00:00:25.025
<i>I look at photos of us when we were happy.</i>

5
00:00:25.108 --> 00:00:28.737
<i>Or the number of texts I've sent</i>
<i>that he's ignored.</i>

6
00:00:28.820 --> 00:00:30.447
<i>Or my personal favorite.</i>

7
00:00:30.530 --> 00:00:33.950
<i>by counting all the things</i>
<i>that I could've done differently.</i>

8
00:00:34.576 --> 00:00:36.578
<i>Maybe I should just go home.</i>

9
00:00:36.661 --> 00:00:38.496
<i>No one hates me at home.</i>

10
00:00:39.205 --> 00:00:40.623
<i>When the pendulum swings</i>

11
00:00:40.707 --> 00:00:43.376
<i>I know it's gonna get me…</i>

12
00:00:43.460 --> 00:00:47.922
<i>God. I can almost smell</i>
<i>Lara Jean's famous chocolate chip cookies.</i>

13
00:00:51.509 --> 00:00:55.555
<i>Wait. I actually </i>can <i>smell</i>
<i>LJ's famous chocolate chip cookies.</i>

14
00:01:02.771 --> 00:01:04.814
What?

15
00:01:04.898 --> 00:01:05.982
Hello?

16
00:01:06.066 --> 00:01:07.317
Hi. sister.

17
00:01:10.278 --> 00:01:12.363
Oh!

18
00:01:12.447 --> 00:01:14.324
I can't believe it. Thank you.

19
00:01:18.453 --> 00:01:20.663
Tell me everything.

20
00:01:21.164 --> 00:01:23.792
- After you take a shower.
- That's mean.

21
00:01:23.875 --> 00:01:25.835
I'm very fragile right now.

22
00:01:26.753 --> 00:01:30.298
Good Lord! I am ripe!

23
00:01:30.381 --> 00:01:32.300
- I'm so sorry.
- It's okay.

24
00:01:32.383 --> 00:01:34.302
- I'm gonna deal with it. Right now.
- Mm-hmm.

25
00:01:34.385 --> 00:01:38.014
Ugh.

26
00:01:42.727 --> 00:01:46.147
And then I fully accused Min Ho
of getting Eunice pregnant.

27
00:01:47.065 --> 00:01:48.983
- Okay. that's not great.
- No.

28
00:01:49.067 --> 00:01:52.403
Um. but isn't this whole thing just.
like. a big misunderstanding?

29
00:01:52.487 --> 00:01:55.115
Sure. One that proves
he should be with somebody else.

30
00:01:55.198 --> 00:01:57.867
Someone unlike me.

31
00:01:57.951 --> 00:01:59.369
What's that supposed to mean?

32
00:01:59.452 --> 00:02:03.957
I don't know. I just… I've always thought
maybe he'd want someone more in his world.

33
00:02:04.040 --> 00:02:06.334
Like a K-pop star.

34
00:02:06.417 --> 00:02:11.422
Okay. if that fool can't see how awesome
you are. then he needs. like. LASIK.

35
00:02:11.506 --> 00:02:13.716
But I should have trusted him.

36
00:02:13.800 --> 00:02:16.136
Hey. didn't he lie to you
about where he was that night?

37
00:02:16.219 --> 00:02:17.554
And… and about the necklace?

38
00:02:17.637 --> 00:02:20.515
Only because he was trying
to be a good friend to Eunice.

39
00:02:20.598 --> 00:02:22.851
the way our mom was
to Yuri's mom back in the day.

40
00:02:22.934 --> 00:02:24.310
Then he should've trusted you.

41
00:02:24.394 --> 00:02:26.604
Well. I don't even trust myself right now.

42
00:02:26.688 --> 00:02:29.524
Like. I was wrong
about Jiwon and Alex being a match.

43
00:02:29.607 --> 00:02:33.069
and then I messed up my entire friendship
with Q in a stupid blurt.

44
00:02:33.153 --> 00:02:35.947
Okay. stop acting like your life is over.

45
00:02:36.030 --> 00:02:37.031
Stop it.

46
00:02:37.115 --> 00:02:40.952
You still have plenty of time left
in your senior year.

47
00:02:41.035 --> 00:02:43.079
And then you're coming
to New York with me.

48
00:02:43.746 --> 00:02:46.166
Speaking of which.
how is your NYU essay going?

49
00:02:46.249 --> 00:02:47.458
Not great.

50
00:02:47.542 --> 00:02:51.504
Wait. what?
When are the early admissions apps due?

51
00:02:51.588 --> 00:02:55.592
Ah. something like.
if I do the time change.

52
00:02:55.675 --> 00:02:56.843
I'm at. like. 12 hours.

53
00:02:57.635 --> 00:03:01.806
Kitty! We talked about applying early
being your best chance of getting in!

54
00:03:01.890 --> 00:03:04.309
I know.
but the essay prompt is impossible.

55
00:03:04.392 --> 00:03:05.852
"Who are you?"

56
00:03:05.935 --> 00:03:08.646
Hello? I don't know
or even like who I am right now!

57
00:03:08.730 --> 00:03:11.065
Okay. your pity party is over.

58
00:03:11.149 --> 00:03:14.402
I had the entire summer
to show you my New York.

59
00:03:14.485 --> 00:03:17.614
And you have. like. less than 24 hours
to show me your Seoul.

60
00:03:17.697 --> 00:03:20.366
And I texted Jiwon.
and she's meeting us for lunch.

61
00:03:20.450 --> 00:03:23.369
Okay. fine. I can handle that.

62
00:03:23.453 --> 00:03:25.705
I thought you were gonna
make me write that essay.

63
00:03:25.788 --> 00:03:28.041
No. yeah. I'm totally gonna
make you write that essay.

64
00:03:28.124 --> 00:03:31.336
But first. we have
to get your head on right. So let's go.

65
00:03:36.591 --> 00:03:38.134
You'd be giving up your dream.

66
00:03:38.218 --> 00:03:44.682
Yeah. Honestly.
when I thought I was pregnant.

67
00:03:44.766 --> 00:03:47.143
I was scared at first.

68
00:03:47.227 --> 00:03:50.939
But when you told me
my career would be over.

69
00:03:51.022 --> 00:03:56.110
it was odd. but suddenly. I felt relieved.

70
00:03:56.861 --> 00:04:03.409
I don't have any privacy.
and always having to be perfect…

71
00:04:03.493 --> 00:04:07.038
it's too hard.

72
00:04:07.121 --> 00:04:09.958
Once I tell my dad.
you know there's no going back.

73
00:04:11.334 --> 00:04:12.585
I know.

74
00:04:12.669 --> 00:04:15.797
But fame isn't what I want.

75
00:04:18.174 --> 00:04:23.471
Min Ho. I'm really sorry.
I didn't know it would turn out like this.

76
00:04:24.472 --> 00:04:26.391
No. you should do what you want.

77
00:04:27.392 --> 00:04:29.018
Thank you so much.

78
00:04:29.102 --> 00:04:33.398
You were a great manager
to me. but an even better friend.

79
00:04:36.317 --> 00:04:39.362
Are you crazy?
She's blowing up the charts.

80
00:04:39.445 --> 00:04:40.989
You have to hold her to her contract.

81
00:04:41.072 --> 00:04:43.866
I can't do that. Dad. Eunice is my friend.

82
00:04:43.950 --> 00:04:45.201
This is just not right.

83
00:04:45.285 --> 00:04:47.370
Then you're not right for this job.

84
00:04:47.453 --> 00:04:50.581
I wanted to believe that you had
what it takes. but clearly you don't.

85
00:04:50.665 --> 00:04:53.209
<i>You're fired.</i>

86
00:04:59.799 --> 00:05:02.302
Sorry again for all the drama
at your dad's restaurant.

87
00:05:02.385 --> 00:05:06.764
Oh. no worries.
I'm sorry that Jin punched you.

88
00:05:06.848 --> 00:05:09.309
Did you figure out
what you're gonna do about this situation?

89
00:05:09.392 --> 00:05:10.643
Let's see.

90
00:05:10.727 --> 00:05:13.062
Jin's ignoring me
when I need to talk to him.

91
00:05:13.146 --> 00:05:16.607
and Marius. who normally
leans strongly towards asshole.

92
00:05:16.691 --> 00:05:18.609
left me a really nice gift.

93
00:05:19.569 --> 00:05:20.570
See my dilemma?

94
00:05:22.071 --> 00:05:25.533
Kitty just got broken up with too.
I'm sure she's down to talk.

95
00:05:25.616 --> 00:05:27.201
She's done enough talking.

96
00:05:27.285 --> 00:05:29.662
It's her big mouth
that got me in this mess.

97
00:05:29.746 --> 00:05:31.289
Yeah.

98
00:05:31.372 --> 00:05:33.166
What do you think I should do?

99
00:05:34.667 --> 00:05:37.295
You want to talk feelings with… me?

100
00:05:38.921 --> 00:05:40.214
Yeah. um…

101
00:05:42.884 --> 00:05:44.510
Were you happy with Jin?

102
00:05:44.594 --> 00:05:46.596
I mean. I thought I was.

103
00:05:46.679 --> 00:05:49.223
but part of me is wondering
if maybe I went all in on Jin

104
00:05:49.307 --> 00:05:51.934
because I was nervous
to admit what I had with Marius.

105
00:05:52.018 --> 00:05:53.102
Mm.

106
00:05:56.856 --> 00:05:59.942
Oh. it's my turn again? Well…

107
00:06:02.278 --> 00:06:04.280
If Kitty had never come to KISS.

108
00:06:05.365 --> 00:06:09.160
I'd have to spend the rest of my life
wondering what could have been.

109
00:06:10.453 --> 00:06:11.454
Right.

110
00:06:12.622 --> 00:06:15.625
Can't know what's at the end of the road
unless you go down it.

111
00:06:15.708 --> 00:06:16.959
Exactly.

112
00:06:17.960 --> 00:06:20.338
Wait. Am I good at this?

113
00:06:24.926 --> 00:06:27.178
Oh yes. Yes.

114
00:06:27.261 --> 00:06:30.640
Truthfully. this reservation is
for the designer Yisoo--

115
00:06:30.723 --> 00:06:31.808
Hello?

116
00:06:31.891 --> 00:06:34.394
Yisoo's craving Impossible again. huh?

117
00:06:34.477 --> 00:06:37.522
- There's a reason that's the name.
- Yeah. tell me about it.

118
00:06:38.523 --> 00:06:41.692
I love this. Who designed it?

119
00:06:41.776 --> 00:06:45.279
Um. that would be me. I thrifted the ties
and turned them into this.

120
00:06:45.363 --> 00:06:47.740
You're submitting your designs
to the contest. right?

121
00:06:47.824 --> 00:06:50.701
Me? No. I'm just an assistant.

122
00:06:50.785 --> 00:06:53.454
So? Everyone who submits
is an up-and-comer.

123
00:06:53.538 --> 00:06:56.833
- I wouldn't even know where to begin.
- Try a pencil and paper.

124
00:06:56.916 --> 00:06:59.043
- Mm.
- You're talented. Yuri.

125
00:06:59.127 --> 00:07:02.463
Do you want to make dinner reservations
for the rest of your life?

126
00:07:03.005 --> 00:07:05.758
- Ready to go?
- Yeah. let me go grab my stuff.

127
00:07:08.010 --> 00:07:11.055
Um. is this a date with Gigi <i>noona?</i>

128
00:07:11.639 --> 00:07:14.851
No. First Kitty and now you.

129
00:07:15.351 --> 00:07:17.645
Does everyone think
I'm just some miserable player?

130
00:07:17.728 --> 00:07:20.565
No. I don't think that.
I know how much you care about Kitty.

131
00:07:21.149 --> 00:07:23.192
I'm sorry about
what happened between you two.

132
00:07:23.276 --> 00:07:27.071
I feel really bad.
Like. I got her all worked up and I--

133
00:07:27.155 --> 00:07:30.575
You didn't make her accuse me of cheating.
or getting Eunice pregnant.

134
00:07:31.534 --> 00:07:33.035
- That was all her.
- Valid.

135
00:07:33.119 --> 00:07:35.788
But for what it's worth.
she feels terrible.

136
00:07:37.415 --> 00:07:38.541
It is what it is.

137
00:07:38.624 --> 00:07:40.001
- Ready?
- Yes.

138
00:07:48.384 --> 00:07:50.511
I can't believe how well you know Seoul.

139
00:07:50.595 --> 00:07:52.472
It's such a great city. isn't it?

140
00:07:52.555 --> 00:07:54.182
And the shopping?

141
00:07:54.265 --> 00:07:58.102
I got tech for Dad. O'Sulloc tea
for Trina. and PDRN cream for Margot.

142
00:07:58.186 --> 00:08:00.897
I also saw you got character socks.

143
00:08:00.980 --> 00:08:03.191
And I know who those are for.

144
00:08:04.108 --> 00:08:07.028
- Does that mean--
- We are not back together.

145
00:08:07.111 --> 00:08:09.530
But Peter is coming to New York.
Just to talk.

146
00:08:10.364 --> 00:08:14.619
Because we are still 5.000 miles apart.
literally and emotionally.

147
00:08:15.119 --> 00:08:18.873
Well. I'm not gonna give up hope.
I know you two are endgame.

148
00:08:18.956 --> 00:08:22.084
Mm. I don't know about that.
but I will keep you posted.

149
00:08:29.258 --> 00:08:31.052
This is a pleasant surprise.

150
00:08:31.844 --> 00:08:34.388
- How's the eye?
- It's healing.

151
00:08:35.640 --> 00:08:40.561
Thank you for the flowers.
That was thoughtful.

152
00:08:40.645 --> 00:08:41.604
Of course.

153
00:08:43.105 --> 00:08:48.236
Look. I think we should talk
about what you told me the other night.

154
00:08:48.861 --> 00:08:52.823
How you came back to KISS for me?

155
00:08:52.907 --> 00:08:54.283
I know that was a lot.

156
00:08:54.367 --> 00:08:57.411
And I definitely overstepped
if you have a new boyfriend.

157
00:08:57.495 --> 00:08:58.913
Had.

158
00:08:59.664 --> 00:09:03.584
I… Actually. I don't even know
what Jin and I are right now.

159
00:09:03.668 --> 00:09:04.877
Well…

160
00:09:06.045 --> 00:09:11.425
I was just gonna go on a ride if…
if you're down.

161
00:09:17.306 --> 00:09:19.725
<i>What does it feel like</i>

162
00:09:19.809 --> 00:09:23.312
<i>Not holding on to memories</i>

163
00:09:23.980 --> 00:09:26.691
<i>'Cause everything's still</i>

164
00:09:26.774 --> 00:09:29.485
<i>Not falling into place</i>

165
00:09:36.075 --> 00:09:38.411
Yuri. what's going on?

166
00:09:38.494 --> 00:09:39.704
Are you okay?

167
00:09:39.787 --> 00:09:42.707
Is this SpongeBob wearing a kilt?

168
00:09:42.790 --> 00:09:46.752
No. it's supposed to be
a yellow puffer and a plaid skirt.

169
00:09:47.753 --> 00:09:51.799
I'm entering this fashion design contest.
and I can't draw to save my own life.

170
00:09:51.882 --> 00:09:53.551
I can draw. remember?

171
00:09:53.634 --> 00:09:55.469
- I'm down to help.
- You'd do that for me?

172
00:09:55.553 --> 00:09:57.430
- Yeah.
- Thank you!

173
00:10:00.641 --> 00:10:02.810
So. Yuri. are you excited for tonight?

174
00:10:02.893 --> 00:10:05.229
Um. I've never been
on a blind date before.

175
00:10:05.313 --> 00:10:07.898
- But it was sweet of you to set me up.
- Mm.

176
00:10:07.982 --> 00:10:08.858
What now?

177
00:10:08.941 --> 00:10:11.944
You remember Sophie?
She's one of the DJs over at Sugar Bar.

178
00:10:12.028 --> 00:10:13.988
I think her and Yuri
will really hit it off.

179
00:10:14.071 --> 00:10:17.325
Yeah. totally.

180
00:10:17.408 --> 00:10:20.870
I think I know what I'm wearing.
but help me with my makeup?

181
00:10:20.953 --> 00:10:22.705
Absolutely.

182
00:10:22.788 --> 00:10:26.334
- I'm thinking neutral shadow. Maybe pink.
- Oh. yes. Love that.

183
00:10:26.834 --> 00:10:28.794
So. you work for a book editor?

184
00:10:28.878 --> 00:10:31.047
- I'm an editorial assistant.
- For now.

185
00:10:31.130 --> 00:10:34.300
She wants to be a writer. she's working on
her first novel. It's amazing.

186
00:10:34.383 --> 00:10:38.137
I don't know about that.
but. uh. I did finally finish it.

187
00:10:38.220 --> 00:10:41.724
Yeah. it's the upside of being single.
I've got lots more free time.

188
00:10:41.807 --> 00:10:44.060
Are you gonna show it to your boss?

189
00:10:44.143 --> 00:10:48.105
Oh no. God. no. I am too scared
to see what she's going to think.

190
00:10:48.689 --> 00:10:50.024
- Hi.
- Hi!

191
00:10:50.107 --> 00:10:51.192
Welcome!

192
00:10:51.275 --> 00:10:55.154
- What would you like to eat?
- One kimchi dumpling.

193
00:10:55.237 --> 00:10:56.489
One <i>pajeon…</i>

194
00:10:56.572 --> 00:10:59.158
- Good with beef tartare?
- Mm-hmm.

195
00:10:59.241 --> 00:11:02.328
And three <i>yukhwae bibimbaps</i>
as well. please.

196
00:11:02.411 --> 00:11:04.789
Oh no. Can you take off
one <i>yukhwae. </i>please?

197
00:11:04.872 --> 00:11:07.291
- So two <i>yukhwae bibimbaps?</i>
- Yes. please. Thank you.

198
00:11:07.917 --> 00:11:09.001
Okay.

199
00:11:09.085 --> 00:11:11.462
- But you love <i>yukhwae.</i>
<i>- </i>I'm not eating raw foods.

200
00:11:11.545 --> 00:11:13.464
Oh. my boss is so afraid of salmonella.

201
00:11:13.547 --> 00:11:16.384
She's pregnant.
so she can't really eat any of that stuff.

202
00:11:20.054 --> 00:11:23.265
Your Korean is getting
really good. Kitty. I'm jealous.

203
00:11:25.393 --> 00:11:28.479
Um. so Kitty says that
you're an amazing teacher.

204
00:11:28.562 --> 00:11:31.232
I bet your <i>halmoni </i>is so. so proud.

205
00:11:31.315 --> 00:11:35.778
Mm-hmm. Excuse me.
I need to go to the bathroom again.

206
00:11:37.988 --> 00:11:41.409
She and Imo-Halmoni
aren't really speaking right now. So…

207
00:11:42.201 --> 00:11:44.745
But she doesn't normally
get that emotional.

208
00:11:44.829 --> 00:11:48.582
Mm. I get it. My boss. she just.
like. cries at the drop of a hat.

209
00:11:49.500 --> 00:11:51.335
- Your pregnant boss?
- Mm-hmm.

210
00:11:51.419 --> 00:11:52.837
- Oh my God.
- What?

211
00:11:53.421 --> 00:11:55.297
Part of why I thought Eunice was pregnant

212
00:11:55.381 --> 00:11:58.384
was because Yuri and I found
a positive pregnancy test at Chuseok.

213
00:11:58.467 --> 00:12:00.302
And Eunice was never pregnant?

214
00:12:00.386 --> 00:12:01.554
- No.
- Uh-uh.

215
00:12:05.766 --> 00:12:09.562
I can't tell
if that was terrifying or exhilarating.

216
00:12:09.645 --> 00:12:12.940
You know I aim to please.
Could you guess where I was taking you?

217
00:12:13.023 --> 00:12:14.483
Yeah. our old spot.

218
00:12:15.443 --> 00:12:18.696
Unless you take
all your sneaky links down here.

219
00:12:18.779 --> 00:12:21.532
We've had lots of good hangs here.

220
00:12:21.615 --> 00:12:24.160
but that doesn't all
have to be in the past.

221
00:12:26.120 --> 00:12:27.955
I want another chance…

222
00:12:29.248 --> 00:12:30.708
with you.

223
00:12:39.508 --> 00:12:41.051
I'm sorry. was it your eye?

224
00:12:41.135 --> 00:12:42.011
No.

225
00:12:44.722 --> 00:12:47.308
Do you remember
the last time you brought me here?

226
00:12:48.225 --> 00:12:51.729
Of course. Our sophomore year. Last day.

227
00:12:53.814 --> 00:12:56.776
I remember asking you
if we could be a real couple.

228
00:12:57.526 --> 00:12:59.612
You made me believe that we could.

229
00:13:00.488 --> 00:13:02.072
And then you ghosted me.

230
00:13:02.156 --> 00:13:04.074
But I came back.

231
00:13:04.700 --> 00:13:07.286
And I came back for you. I've changed. Q.

232
00:13:08.037 --> 00:13:11.749
Yeah. When <i>you </i>were finally ready.

233
00:13:12.333 --> 00:13:14.126
Even though I had a boyfriend.

234
00:13:15.711 --> 00:13:18.088
Not everything can be on your timeline.

235
00:13:19.757 --> 00:13:21.467
Things are different now.

236
00:13:22.843 --> 00:13:23.844
I've changed too.

237
00:13:26.680 --> 00:13:29.058
And a lot of that is because of Jin.

238
00:13:29.141 --> 00:13:30.810
So that's it. then?

239
00:13:32.603 --> 00:13:34.396
You're not even gonna try?

240
00:13:35.773 --> 00:13:37.316
We've been down this road before.

241
00:13:39.401 --> 00:13:40.569
This is where it ends.

242
00:13:44.990 --> 00:13:46.659
<i>Pay attention</i>

243
00:13:50.621 --> 00:13:54.583
You seriously thought I'd enjoy this?

244
00:13:54.667 --> 00:13:58.212
Ugh. Can we take a break? My hands are
gonna need a paraffin dip after this.

245
00:13:58.295 --> 00:14:01.215
Aww! If your nail breaks.
bill me for the manicure.

246
00:14:01.298 --> 00:14:03.759
Forget the bill.
I don't think I'll make it to the top.

247
00:14:03.843 --> 00:14:05.719
That's why I brought you here.

248
00:14:06.554 --> 00:14:08.597
- I heard what happened with your dad.
- Yeah.

249
00:14:08.681 --> 00:14:11.600
It just felt nice to have him
believe in me for a change.

250
00:14:11.684 --> 00:14:15.145
He should. You are a good person. Min Ho.

251
00:14:15.229 --> 00:14:18.274
- Tell that to Kitty.
- Oh. so you still care what she thinks?

252
00:14:18.357 --> 00:14:22.152
I just can't get past it. The trust thing.

253
00:14:22.236 --> 00:14:26.490
She says she was in her own head.
worried she didn't fit in my world.

254
00:14:26.574 --> 00:14:28.784
But I never made her feel like that.

255
00:14:28.868 --> 00:14:31.412
It… doesn't mean she didn't feel that way.

256
00:14:32.705 --> 00:14:38.377
Your whole world is intimidating.
Red carpets. K-pop stars…

257
00:14:38.878 --> 00:14:41.839
- I mean. your own dad just fired you.
- True.

258
00:14:41.922 --> 00:14:44.758
Look. I don't know what to do
about you and Kitty. but I do know

259
00:14:44.842 --> 00:14:47.219
that you don't need to take
the path set out by your dad.

260
00:14:47.303 --> 00:14:50.180
Right. Then what?

261
00:14:50.264 --> 00:14:53.267
I mean. you produced
the hell out of Eunice's music video.

262
00:14:54.143 --> 00:14:57.646
Maybe your talents are bigger
than just controlling artists' lives.

263
00:14:57.730 --> 00:15:02.067
Maybe. But without my dad's support.
it'd be pretty hard to make it.

264
00:15:02.151 --> 00:15:05.279
You know. it's easy
to take the obvious path.

265
00:15:06.196 --> 00:15:10.534
But the riskier one
is way more satisfying.

266
00:15:11.201 --> 00:15:12.286
Wanna give it a go?

267
00:15:15.205 --> 00:15:17.541
All right.

268
00:15:18.250 --> 00:15:20.044
No. I cannot get involved. LJ.

269
00:15:20.127 --> 00:15:22.463
I have overstepped
so many times this semester.

270
00:15:22.546 --> 00:15:24.924
If I do it one more time.
Jiwon might never speak to me again.

271
00:15:25.007 --> 00:15:27.718
No. okay. Kitty. I know you better
than anyone else in the world.

272
00:15:27.801 --> 00:15:30.429
You are a good person
with good intentions.

273
00:15:30.512 --> 00:15:32.681
And Jiwon might
really need your help right now.

274
00:15:32.765 --> 00:15:33.766
Help with what?

275
00:15:39.939 --> 00:15:41.690
I found a positive pregnancy test
at Chuseok.

276
00:15:41.774 --> 00:15:42.816
We think it might be yours.

277
00:15:42.900 --> 00:15:45.986
And you don't have to say if it was.
but we are here for you.

278
00:15:54.912 --> 00:15:56.830
What am I gonna do?

279
00:15:57.957 --> 00:16:00.793
My <i>halmoni </i>and I fought so hard
for me to get here.

280
00:16:00.876 --> 00:16:05.089
and instead of proving
I could handle myself. I got pregnant.

281
00:16:05.965 --> 00:16:09.134
And now I've ruined my life and his too.

282
00:16:09.218 --> 00:16:11.470
No. you have not ruined anything.

283
00:16:12.054 --> 00:16:13.555
Have you told the father?

284
00:16:13.639 --> 00:16:16.850
An unplanned pregnancy will be
extra-triggering for him because…

285
00:16:18.644 --> 00:16:21.730
Because he was unplanned himself.

286
00:16:24.191 --> 00:16:26.485
It's Alex. isn't it?

287
00:16:28.278 --> 00:16:30.656
Yeah. Uh…

288
00:16:31.198 --> 00:16:36.286
We met at summer orientation.
and I wasn't into him at first.

289
00:16:36.370 --> 00:16:39.999
He's so earnest. and that accent…

290
00:16:40.791 --> 00:16:42.835
But I love him.

291
00:16:43.419 --> 00:16:45.337
This is wonderful.

292
00:16:45.421 --> 00:16:48.799
But his dad is my boss.
and we couldn't get caught.

293
00:16:48.882 --> 00:16:52.428
so we kept it secret
and played up that we didn't get along.

294
00:16:53.679 --> 00:16:55.305
I'm so sorry. Kitty.

295
00:16:56.432 --> 00:16:58.392
No. I… I've been such a hypocrite.

296
00:16:58.475 --> 00:16:59.518
No.

297
00:16:59.601 --> 00:17:02.062
I… I was so hard on you
for focusing on a boy.

298
00:17:02.146 --> 00:17:05.065
when I was busy
focusing on my own romance.

299
00:17:05.149 --> 00:17:08.068
No. It's okay.

300
00:17:08.152 --> 00:17:10.571
I know this is scary right now.

301
00:17:10.654 --> 00:17:14.074
but if I've learned
one thing about you this semester.

302
00:17:14.700 --> 00:17:19.747
it's that you are brilliant and so strong.

303
00:17:21.415 --> 00:17:23.876
And honestly. you're a total baddie.

304
00:17:23.959 --> 00:17:26.795
And I'm sure that's why Alex fell for you.

305
00:17:27.296 --> 00:17:30.841
And I know he's gonna be there for you.

306
00:17:32.509 --> 00:17:33.927
And we're gonna be there too.

307
00:17:35.971 --> 00:17:36.972
Thank you.

308
00:17:44.855 --> 00:17:45.898
Thanks.

309
00:17:47.983 --> 00:17:50.152
Hey. What's going on?

310
00:17:50.778 --> 00:17:54.031
- You've seemed off all day.
- Right.

311
00:17:56.075 --> 00:17:59.912
Okay. um. I wanna be mature about this.

312
00:18:01.371 --> 00:18:05.667
You setting my ex up
on dates is just… weird.

313
00:18:09.296 --> 00:18:11.590
Because you still have feelings for her?

314
00:18:11.673 --> 00:18:14.218
No. no. no. no. I just…

315
00:18:15.385 --> 00:18:18.514
Yuri was my first love.

316
00:18:20.432 --> 00:18:22.518
And I think
that I'm always gonna care about her.

317
00:18:24.728 --> 00:18:26.480
I'm sorry. I'm trying to be honest.

318
00:18:26.563 --> 00:18:29.775
I know you are.
I'm glad we're being honest.

319
00:18:31.235 --> 00:18:33.195
That's the healthiest way to break up.

320
00:18:33.278 --> 00:18:36.573
What? No. I thought
we were being. like. evolved here.

321
00:18:36.657 --> 00:18:39.159
- I didn't say I wanted to break up.
- Look.

322
00:18:39.701 --> 00:18:41.662
I deserve to be with someone

323
00:18:41.745 --> 00:18:45.457
who's excited to see me
every time I walk into a room.

324
00:18:46.166 --> 00:18:47.793
The way you are when you see Yuri.

325
00:18:48.710 --> 00:18:52.714
Maybe I was setting Yuri up because.

326
00:18:53.215 --> 00:18:59.847
deep down. I knew you felt this way.
and… I didn't want her to be available.

327
00:19:00.848 --> 00:19:07.729
But… if I'm feeling insecure
and you're feeling…

328
00:19:09.356 --> 00:19:11.608
a little bit… jealous?

329
00:19:12.818 --> 00:19:14.903
Maybe we're doing something wrong here?

330
00:19:24.746 --> 00:19:26.290
Hey. what are you doing?

331
00:19:26.790 --> 00:19:29.168
I just got an email from Seoul National.

332
00:19:30.544 --> 00:19:31.712
I didn't get in.

333
00:19:33.714 --> 00:19:36.258
Really? You're the first in our class.

334
00:19:36.758 --> 00:19:37.801
Mm.

335
00:19:39.178 --> 00:19:43.640
I was always worried I wouldn't be
able to go because of the money.

336
00:19:45.642 --> 00:19:48.645
I never even thought I wouldn't get in.

337
00:19:51.899 --> 00:19:56.069
Yuri asked me the other day
if I had my own dream.

338
00:19:58.030 --> 00:19:59.656
Dream? You have one?

339
00:19:59.740 --> 00:20:00.908
Mm.

340
00:20:01.408 --> 00:20:02.618
I do.

341
00:20:02.701 --> 00:20:03.994
Uh…

342
00:20:04.077 --> 00:20:05.329
But it's a little crazy.

343
00:20:05.412 --> 00:20:06.788
Is it music. by chance?

344
00:20:07.664 --> 00:20:09.374
How did you know?

345
00:20:09.458 --> 00:20:11.919
Last year you held yourself back
from the stage.

346
00:20:12.002 --> 00:20:13.587
but you ended up doing really well.

347
00:20:15.631 --> 00:20:17.049
I have an idea…

348
00:20:20.052 --> 00:20:23.513
Wouldn't it be fun
if you and I made music together?

349
00:20:23.597 --> 00:20:26.558
It would be fun. of course.
but is that as easy as it sounds?

350
00:20:26.642 --> 00:20:29.478
It won't be easy.
but it's something you have a taste for.

351
00:20:29.561 --> 00:20:31.480
What do you say?

352
00:20:38.487 --> 00:20:40.197
Chalk. I'm sorry.

353
00:20:44.993 --> 00:20:47.871
Okay. she's telling him.

354
00:20:53.001 --> 00:20:54.086
Mm!

355
00:20:55.671 --> 00:20:56.672
Wow.

356
00:20:58.006 --> 00:21:01.551
To think Mom set up Jiwon's parents
all those years ago.

357
00:21:02.302 --> 00:21:05.722
and now you're bringing
Jiwon and Alex back together.

358
00:21:06.223 --> 00:21:09.601
I think if Mom could see
you now. she'd be so proud of you.

359
00:21:10.185 --> 00:21:11.186
I know I am.

360
00:21:12.354 --> 00:21:13.689
Do you really mean that?

361
00:21:15.190 --> 00:21:19.027
Kitty. at 16. you flew across the world.

362
00:21:19.903 --> 00:21:25.534
You learned a new language. and you built
a rich life for yourself in Seoul.

363
00:21:26.868 --> 00:21:29.454
How can you not see how amazing that is?

364
00:21:29.538 --> 00:21:32.374
I mean. it's what you did
when you went to New York.

365
00:21:33.375 --> 00:21:36.003
God. it was so hard for me to go.

366
00:21:36.086 --> 00:21:40.007
I mean. I had never been on my own
'cause I'd always had my sisters.

367
00:21:40.090 --> 00:21:44.970
I was so scared to put myself out there.
but not you.

368
00:21:45.053 --> 00:21:46.847
You're the brave one.

369
00:21:46.930 --> 00:21:51.893
The leaps that you take
and the lengths that you go to for others.

370
00:21:52.936 --> 00:21:54.354
that's what makes you. you.

371
00:21:54.980 --> 00:21:57.566
And your heart is
always in the right place.

372
00:21:58.233 --> 00:21:59.693
Thank you. sister.

373
00:22:09.161 --> 00:22:10.537
<i>Who am I?</i>

374
00:22:10.620 --> 00:22:14.082
<i>For better or worse. I'm someone</i>
<i>who's not afraid to take a leap.</i>

375
00:22:14.166 --> 00:22:17.127
<i>When I'm lucky.</i>
<i>I find a net there to catch me.</i>

376
00:22:17.210 --> 00:22:20.714
<i>like my incredible family</i>
<i>who's always there for me.</i>

377
00:22:21.340 --> 00:22:25.635
<i>But even when I've made mistakes</i>
<i>and fallen. I've been stretched.</i>

378
00:22:27.929 --> 00:22:32.225
<i>Stretched by an amazing city that</i>
<i>I will forever consider a second home.</i>

379
00:22:32.309 --> 00:22:35.103
<i>It's taught me things</i>
<i>I never knew I needed to learn.</i>

380
00:22:35.687 --> 00:22:38.523
<i>Like how to show up for people</i>
<i>when they need me.</i>

381
00:22:39.483 --> 00:22:42.569
<i>How to be open</i>
<i>to unexpected relationships.</i>

382
00:22:44.905 --> 00:22:50.452
<i>Or how to pivot when relationships turn</i>
<i>out to be different than what I expected.</i>

383
00:23:01.088 --> 00:23:02.589
<i>It takes courage to leap.</i>

384
00:23:02.672 --> 00:23:05.509
<i>but it also takes courage</i>
<i>to pick yourself up when you fall</i>

385
00:23:05.592 --> 00:23:08.261
<i>and keep going. to grow.</i>

386
00:23:08.345 --> 00:23:10.680
<i>But that's exactly what I intend to do.</i>

387
00:23:10.764 --> 00:23:13.975
<i>'cause I know there's</i>
<i>so much more of myself to discover.</i>

388
00:23:14.476 --> 00:23:18.397
<i>I'm not done leaping yet.</i>
<i>I'm barely getting started.</i>

389
00:23:26.238 --> 00:23:27.572
I love it. Kitty.

390
00:23:28.073 --> 00:23:30.117
If this doesn't get you in.
they are fools.

391
00:23:30.742 --> 00:23:33.078
Thank you. For everything.

392
00:23:33.161 --> 00:23:34.204
Okay.

393
00:23:36.164 --> 00:23:39.292
Ah. okay. Here we go.

394
00:23:50.846 --> 00:23:51.847
What's wrong?

395
00:23:54.558 --> 00:23:59.271
Early decision feels so… binding.

396
00:23:59.771 --> 00:24:06.278
Like. if I do get in…
then I'm going to NYU next year.

397
00:24:07.195 --> 00:24:08.697
I thought that's what you wanted.

398
00:24:09.281 --> 00:24:13.326
Yeah. I love NYU. and I would be
so excited to go to New York.

399
00:24:13.410 --> 00:24:15.912
and be closer to you and home. But…

400
00:24:17.247 --> 00:24:20.125
Seoul has become such a big part of me.

401
00:24:20.208 --> 00:24:22.836
And I can imagine myself staying here too.

402
00:24:22.919 --> 00:24:24.129
I get that.

403
00:24:25.005 --> 00:24:27.215
I mean. you built
a whole life for yourself here.

404
00:24:31.761 --> 00:24:33.472
And Min Ho's here.

405
00:24:36.892 --> 00:24:40.270
I would be lying

406
00:24:40.353 --> 00:24:46.610
if I didn't say a part of me…
still hopes we work out.

407
00:24:49.321 --> 00:24:53.783
Still hopes that we're… endgame.

408
00:24:54.826 --> 00:24:57.204
The way I know you and Peter are.

409
00:25:00.624 --> 00:25:03.126
I don't know what's gonna happen
between you and Min Ho.

410
00:25:04.377 --> 00:25:07.631
I don't know what's gonna happen
between me and Peter.

411
00:25:08.507 --> 00:25:11.218
But we can't just stop living our lives.

412
00:25:12.344 --> 00:25:16.181
I think that we have to follow our hearts

413
00:25:16.264 --> 00:25:20.101
and trust that it will lead us
to our next great adventure.

414
00:25:28.276 --> 00:25:29.986
Okay. here goes nothing.

415
00:25:37.744 --> 00:25:40.747
- I love you.
- I love you. Kitty.

416
00:25:46.086 --> 00:25:50.215
Hi. sorry I'm late. I hope you weren't
working too hard without me.

417
00:25:50.298 --> 00:25:53.468
Not too hard.
How did your date with Sophie go?

418
00:25:53.552 --> 00:25:56.471
Not bad. yeah. She asked me out again.

419
00:25:56.555 --> 00:25:57.722
You gonna go?

420
00:25:57.806 --> 00:25:59.766
Yeah. she's nice.

421
00:26:00.267 --> 00:26:03.770
And your girlfriend has good taste.
But we already knew that.

422
00:26:05.855 --> 00:26:08.650
That's great. I'm happy for you.

423
00:26:09.693 --> 00:26:11.278
Show me what you've been working on.

424
00:26:11.903 --> 00:26:14.656
You remember this one?

425
00:26:14.739 --> 00:26:17.450
Wait. no. You fixed SpongeBob.

426
00:26:17.534 --> 00:26:20.745
- A little tweaking. but it's your vision.
- It's so good.

427
00:26:22.914 --> 00:26:25.041
Just hear me out. Please.

428
00:26:34.259 --> 00:26:37.262
This summer. I was confused.

429
00:26:37.345 --> 00:26:41.891
It was before you visited me.
and I was lonely at USC. and…

430
00:26:43.101 --> 00:26:44.019
I slipped.

431
00:26:45.687 --> 00:26:48.064
But I'm not confused anymore. Jin.

432
00:26:48.815 --> 00:26:50.400
You…

433
00:26:51.735 --> 00:26:53.111
You are my person.

434
00:26:55.363 --> 00:26:56.990
Can we please start over?

435
00:26:58.199 --> 00:27:02.579
Maybe we can talk about
what that would look like.

436
00:27:02.662 --> 00:27:04.748
As long as there are
no more secrets between us.

437
00:27:04.831 --> 00:27:06.291
I promise.

438
00:27:06.374 --> 00:27:08.752
I took the time
to go down that road with Marius.

439
00:27:08.835 --> 00:27:11.713
but the choice is clear. I choose you.

440
00:27:11.796 --> 00:27:13.965
Down the road? What does that mean?

441
00:27:14.049 --> 00:27:15.592
Nothing. That we…

442
00:27:16.092 --> 00:27:19.721
We rode to our old spot. Let me finish.

443
00:27:19.804 --> 00:27:23.767
That place. it made me realize
that you were the one that I want.

444
00:27:24.643 --> 00:27:26.936
Q. I didn't need
to spend time with someone else

445
00:27:27.020 --> 00:27:29.606
or go on some romantic ride
to know you were the one.

446
00:27:29.689 --> 00:27:32.525
- I know. and I'm sorry.
- No. I changed who I was for you.

447
00:27:33.318 --> 00:27:35.487
I used to be the guy
who wouldn't let anyone in.

448
00:27:35.570 --> 00:27:37.656
but I trusted you and I let you in.

449
00:27:39.199 --> 00:27:41.284
I'll never make that mistake again.

450
00:27:48.833 --> 00:27:50.168
I wish you could stay longer.

451
00:27:50.251 --> 00:27:54.839
Me too. but I have to get back before
my boss realizes I do not have norovirus.

452
00:27:54.923 --> 00:27:56.841
And you have to get to Korean Lit.

453
00:27:56.925 --> 00:28:02.138
You know. you could distract your boss
by sending her your manuscript.

454
00:28:02.222 --> 00:28:03.390
I already did.

455
00:28:03.473 --> 00:28:05.308
Wait. what? Are you serious?

456
00:28:06.184 --> 00:28:07.519
Yeah.

457
00:28:07.602 --> 00:28:09.020
I sent it last night.

458
00:28:09.104 --> 00:28:12.482
I feel like I was just so scared.
you know. to do it because.

459
00:28:13.483 --> 00:28:15.860
like. everything would
just become so real.

460
00:28:15.944 --> 00:28:18.154
Like the future.

461
00:28:18.988 --> 00:28:24.244
New York. and I really do not know
what the future holds for Peter and I.

462
00:28:25.745 --> 00:28:29.916
But I can't not bet on myself.

463
00:28:29.999 --> 00:28:32.627
And that is
why you are the perfect role model.

464
00:28:33.336 --> 00:28:35.714
I can't believe I'm going to be related

465
00:28:35.797 --> 00:28:37.799
to a <i>New York Times </i>bestselling author.

466
00:28:38.425 --> 00:28:40.135
I love you. Kitty.

467
00:28:40.218 --> 00:28:42.137
I love you too. LJ.

468
00:28:42.220 --> 00:28:45.432
Please don't make me fly
across the world to fix your life again.

469
00:28:45.515 --> 00:28:46.766
I'll try my best.

470
00:28:48.059 --> 00:28:50.061
Okay. you're gonna be late. Go. go.

471
00:28:50.145 --> 00:28:52.105
- Oh my God.
- You're gonna be late. Go. go.

472
00:28:52.188 --> 00:28:53.648
Yo. Min Ho!

473
00:28:59.946 --> 00:29:03.908
Yeah. um…
Why don't you go ahead? I'll catch up.

474
00:29:08.329 --> 00:29:09.330
Lara Jean.

475
00:29:10.081 --> 00:29:11.082
Hi. Min Ho.

476
00:29:14.252 --> 00:29:15.253
How's Kitty?

477
00:29:16.838 --> 00:29:17.839
Honestly…

478
00:29:20.216 --> 00:29:21.217
She's great.

